## Project Structure

This is a Vite + React + TypeScript project. Follow these conventions at all times:

### Layout
Use standard responsive breakpoints and let layouts adapt to the viewport width.

### Assets
- All images go in /public/images/
- All Lottie animation files go in /public/animations/
- Reference images as src="/images/filename.jpg" — never import them into components
- Reference Lottie files as src="/animations/filename.json"

### Components
- All components go in /src/components/
- Each component gets its own file
- Do not co-locate images or assets inside /src/components/

### Styles
- Global CSS variables and resets live in /src/globals.css
- No Tailwind, no CSS-in-JS, no UI libraries — plain CSS only

### Design System
- Background: #1a1a1a
- Menu title: #cccccc
- Menu items default: #7b7b7b
- Menu items hover: #eeeeee

- Section headings: #eeeeee
- Caption: #7b7b7b
- Summary: #eeeeee
- Subtitles: #d2d2d2
- ListHeadings: #d2d2d2
- Body copy: #999999

Set font-family to 'Inter', sans-serif.
Use font-weight: 500 for medium text and font-weight: 700 for bold text.

- Menu items: font-weight: 700
- Section headings: font-weight: 500
- Caption: font-weight: 500
- Summary: font-weight: 500
- Subtitles:font-weight: 500
- ListHeadings: font-weight: 500
- Body copy: font-weight: 500

For menu icons made of three lines 1 px #2a2a2a, on hover only change the color of the middle line to #eeeeee, not the entire icon.
Keep the other two lines unchanged.
Use the existing SVG paths or separate elements so only the targeted line is styled on hover.

### Dependencies
- Lottie player: @lottiefiles/react-lottie-player
- No other UI or animation libraries unless explicitly asked